Hi, Given below our experience, we visited this place yesterday evening. Its realy a over hyped place, Food price is too much compare to quantity n teste. Being a Awadhi Restaurent they dont know n dont serve Dum Biriyani n proper toonduri preparation. We ordered Chicken Biriyani at S$25 which is  just like Masala Biriyani available in any indian food court at $8. Rice quality also not fine. Some yellow colour rice fr one person quantiy with 4-5 pieces small chicken n much cooking well. Yes they dont use ghee or cow milk fat fr cooking. No use of zafran or safron. We order Galawati kebab, price is $24, four moderate size kebab served in a big plate wth little cheese :-) , kebab was soft n flavourfull of mithi aatar but quantity is little only also mutton was less in it.. They served little quantity in a big plare as they r charging high price, not a single place of salad with Kebab but given lil cheese with it which is wrong choice. Apart from that we ordered some veg preparations which were so so kind. What is missing here the touch of Awadh but they r presenting themself as Fine Royal Dinning of Awadh.. its totally miss guiding customer. When we were having food around 60 people came with tour company to have indian buffet food, yes thats why they r running there business here.. also they serve few indian chinese foods also though we have not tried it. They charge 10% service tax but we hardly got any service there, Every time our glass emptied we have to look fr them n asked for water then we got water.. We got 2 buckets of papad as complementary.. There is no wash basin in shop as its in a mall so u have to go out to wash ur hand or naturs call. Overall its not at all Fine Awadhi dining restaurent they r miss guiding people by FB Ad. We will not recomend this restaurent to have any food at all sorry to say. Thank u

We went to this restaurant last September to have authentic Indian cuisine. Even though it is expensive than other Indian restaurants in the area, we decided to go hoping the food would be nice. At the time we arrived, there was a private function going on and it was very loud and a couple of people were singing loud. We ordered 1 Multani Kadhai Paneer, 1 Chicken Biryani, and 2 Naans. It took about 45 minutes to take our order, which can be considered as ok, but surprisingly they took the dishes we hadnt ordered as well. When we were looking menu, we asked the staff what kind of dish is Achari Paneer Tikka and they said it comes as a starter. So we didnt order it, but they prepared it and added it to our order. Since we clearly said we didnt want that in our meal, we asked them to take it back. But the staff were too arrogant and said however we have to pay for it. We ended up paying nearly SGD100 just for 3 dishes. And the worst thing was the taste of the food, Chicken Biryani was smelly and undercooked. Paneer was too thick and Naans were too dry and flakey. I wonder why they are serving their customers too badly. Honestly, we thought we could have eaten from just a convenience store for better food than there

Arrived on a Sunday at 3.30 pm. Serving staff, Rosia, was very friendly and helpful as I was looking through the menu, not knowing what to order. She recommended the $25.90 brunch with 1 Chaat/ Appetizer unlimited and 1 main course. I told her I do not like sweet food and she recommended the Samosa Chaat, a potato filled crisps with yogurt and chutney. It was delicious. My main course is the Mutton Bun Kebab, with minced mutton patty fried to golden brown, caramelized onions and buttered bun. This is fabulous too, not too salty but bun is a little tough, not for the elderly who have trouble chewing. The mutton patty is nice. I finished the appetizer and had a third of the bun then take away the leftover. I also ordered the Martini Bianco $12 as Rosia said it isnt as sweet as Martini Rosso. The drink is nice. After dinner, I ordered another Martini Negroni $17, which is supposedly a stronger drink that is more popular with guys. I like it too, strong and balance. For gals, they may want some lime juice in it. Total is about $65 as I had two alcohol drinks. It is still value for money, especially the brunch that is available on Sat, Sun and Public Holiday from 10.30 am to 4.30 pm. Highly recommend this restaurant to all.

Rip off. Very ordinary ambiance and very ordinary food. The waiter recommended tandoori prawns. Off menu. The preparation was ok, nothing great. But it was priced SGD34++  ridiculous.
Awesome place n amazing food
Superb food great service. Awesome place.

I m kinda an expert of the Indian Menu .. the spices, the rice and the overall cooking is a bit heavier than normal. This spot is not really as described as a royal India food. The seatings, the smell and the loud music has nothing to do with royalty The cooking style and the overall experience has to deal with a lot of improvements And by they way the prices are easy higher than the normal Indian
Horrible food. Sabz Galawat was very salty. Taste was very bad. It is pricey and below average. Extremely disappointed.
Expensive and not so good. Can find better options in Singapore
Not as advertised.
One of the most beautiful Indian restaurants I have tried I recommend the meat biryani + green salona with white rice

The briyani was a disappointment. I read the reviews before choosing this shop, and someone stated that the briyani was amazing, which made me wanted to try it. The chicken was not cooked properly, tasteless, can see brownish colour meat which does not looks fresh, rice was pale, just was colorful rice but tasteless. Only can get the chutney taste which was given together with the rice. Am not sure hows the other food choices, but it is a BIG NO for briyani. Is my honest review, because I do not want other briyani lovers out there to share my disappointment. Previously I went Shakuntala restaurant, although their briyani rice is a bit pale but their chicken is thoroughly cooked, rich with aromas and flavours. I should have gone there again, rather than trying out Awadhs.
Very expensive. Very very little portion of meat compared to the price. I am not sure whether I unfortunately had such a bad experience. In anyway I will never ever visit this restaurant again.

Great food but the loud live music ruined the evening. They have a smallish place and very loud live music on Fri/Sat more suitable for a dance place. Don t go there on a weekend unless you are alone. The food was good so perhaps consider ordering on Grab instead.
Awesome Food. Very attentive and polite service staff. Nice ambience.

Excellent place and ambience. Very very friendly and sweet staffs. I called them and told them about my parents anniversary. They made is very special and heartwarming. Kudos to Awadh Team and the staff. Great going.

Lovely food. We had butter Chicken and Roti This was gr8. For starters ordered chicken chandi kebab. Though it was good it was bland for my taste. Could have been slightly spicy. Overall good experience. Would come again.

AVOID THIS RESTAURANT We went for a casual lunch on a Sunday afternoon (May 2022). Deeply unimpressed by the food, service and experience. Food : Pathetic taste. We ordered Dahi Kebab, Seekh Kebab and Subz Biryani. Dahi Kebab was extremely oily, bland and nothing like it should taste. Subz Biryani had no spice and salt. Seekh Kebab was the only saviour with decent taste. Service : Zero customer orientation. They were busy upselling drinks to us when we were talking to them about food quality. One person listened to what we said and then started speaking to another colleague. No apology, no offer to change / redress concerns and absolutely no desire to make our experience better. Live music was really good and made everything somewhat bearable. IF YOU HAVE A REASONABLY EVOLVED PALATE FOR INDIAN FOOD, PLEASE DO NOT WASTE YOUR TIME AND MONEY HERE.
perfect service n perfect food
The taste of the food was not so authentic.

Love love love! Absolutely delicious food and I had so much fun!! The food is amazing on its own, but the ambience, the customer service, the authenticity, all factors were fulfilled! Definitely the most recommended on the list
I went there twice and the food is amazing.The waiters are also very nice and sweet.Defo reccommended
Very good food and music!
Ok food and ambiance
Very expensive place.... Ambiance was good , food was tasting ok not dat good
Lovely food.

If you want to get mad yourself visit to this restaurant. I was looking for decent Indian food in orchard and visited this place on Saturday evening.  For my surprise restaurant is so noisy with loud music and DJ talking nonsense in singlish as he wants to entertain customers. So loud noise in small place you wont be able to eat comfortably with Family. I was so disappointed by the overall atmosphere. You can t enjoy food in such noisy place with family eventually I left before ordering food. This is not place for Family Dining out.

Definitely an under-rated restaurant, rang mahal food at a fraction of the cost. the paneer is heavenly. the chicken with cashew has lovely wok hei with an etheral light cashew cream sauce. Mr Kamran was very kind to lower the heat in the dishes, and made excellent recommendation, specifically the minced lamb patties (also called kebabs in Lucknow). We had the Pasqua Amarone that was kinda sweet, that went really well with the spicy food. will definitely return, and may well be my go to place for indian cuisine.
We placed an order for lunch at noon and nothing was delivered. Finally at 3:30 pm we decided to cancel the order. What a waste of time.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear guest, were sorry for the inconvenience caused. We noticed  that you have placed your order from a third party platform and not with our internal delivery options. In this case we have limited control over delivery since delivery is taken care by a third party food delivery parter with whom you have placed the order.  Going forward, please make sure to place your orders from our website - order.theawadh.com so that we can ensure timely delivery of your order. Looking forward to serving you, thank you!

detailed_reviews.review_text: Lousy overpriced food, they position themselves as awas greasy and quite tasteless, prices are ridiculous, service is okayish - they try and cross sell everything steer clear of this place

Went there with my friends for dinner. Very friendly staff. Very helpful too in helping us with the menu since we not so familiar. Food was awesome to us. The recommended naan by the supervisor there goes well with the food we ordered. Very hard to spot the restaurant. We really enjoyed our meal. My favorite and personal choice was the Bhuna Gosht.

We came here for the food and they did not disappoint. Superb quality, our taste buds were in a party and were so happy! We ordered the ff dishes: -AWADHI BHUNA GOSHT -MURGH LUCKNAWI MASALA -LAHORI KADHAI MURG -SAAG GOSHT NAAN recommendation from them: -AWADHI MAGAJ NAAN -GARLIC BUTTER NAAN -BUTTER NAAN Will definitely recommend to friends and come back to try the other dishes. Looking forward on our next meal.

Unique range of food choices but if you are unfamiliar with Indian cuisine , you ll need to be prepared by doing your research to know what you are ordering. Staff lacks the understanding of customers request and would strongly voice their preferences upon responding to customer queries.
tasty food and good service..!! I mostly tried the non veg menu.. cant say much abut Veg
Delicious lamb dish, but very expensive at $27. The plain naan at $6 is also too expensive. Theres nothing special about it. Will I go back there? No.

Absolutely Horrible! Weve been waiting for our food for the past 2 hours!!! Literally paying for food which has been prepared 2 hours back and still on the road. Continuously making excuses. This is after ordering from their website. The service of the restaurant has gone down miserably. The manager, Kamran on the phone said, we cant do anything about the delivery, the food is not the restaurants responsibility after it leaves from here. All this after the restaurant charged a delivery premium and a surcharge! Well done.
Tasteless! even a simple tea taste like hot water ! i would have given a -1 if i could
Bhuna Ghosht and Goat items are good. Chat was okay.. Vegetarian curry- Kofta was uninspiring

An authentic Indian restaurant where you can try different varieties of slow cooked non-veg food. My daughter loves their Kalmi Kebab and Ghost Dum Biryani. The ambience is so great especially when there s lesser crowd. They have a good collection of mocktails and cocktails. A lovely place to have some peaceful time with family with a fine dining experience.

Had dinner with my friend. Courteous staff. Quality and quantity was great. Enjoyed Authentic North Indian tasty food. Surprised to see real mango and strawberries in the respective lassi instead of syrups in the month of January. Wonder how did they manage to get mangoes in Jan. Bit costly though.

We tried this place with a group of friends because the menu looked interesting and the specialize in Lucknow cuisine. While I cannot comment from the perspective of an expert in how the food ought to taste, we thoroughly enjoyed the meal and also found it to be reasonable value for money. The service was fine. I d go back to try more dishes.
Nice food and service.
love thr food altho abit ex, quite cool, ill go here again someday

Bad food, avoid it! We ordered their Galawat Kebab, Kadhai paneer and Lahori chicken. The only slightly edible dish was the lahori chicken. The kadhai paneer and the lamb kebab competed with each other for the worst dish ever made! And ridiculously priced for the Low quality food. Avoid like the plague !
Nice ambience,  luv the food

Horrible Food today. Its more expensive than other Indian restaurant in Singapore... So expected much more and better quality food. It was very ordinary. Do not waste your money in this place. I ordered food many times before ...the food was good then. Maybe they changed their cook.
The food is neither tasty nor authentic.
Food good. But too expensive. Also, when they bring out a Sizzler for a table.  Its all smoke all around for a few mins. Drinks and food over priced.

I tried this restaurant on my fifth wedding anniversary because we didn t get the reservation to any other suitable places. Food was good there, especially Paneer tikka, as it was super soft and flavorful. Other than this, we also had kadhai paneer, samosa, and lassi, but it was not as I expected. Lassi was so watery and had some bitter taste. The service was good. I was a little disappointed because before going I called them and told them about my special occasion, and they said yes you could come we will give you a special table or something. But they didnt do anything special. They had lit candles on all tables except ours, and I had to ask them to light the candle at least. Our celebration didnt go as expected.
Very Authentic and classy North Indian food with a great Personalised service .
Great food, Excellent Hospitality!!

It was our first time visiting an indian restaurant, and we thoroughly enjoyed the food!! Ambience and service were great. Their butter chicken was the best i ve ever had! Garlic naan was extremely good too. We also ordered a fish fillet dish, which had a unique flavour but was too salty for our liking. It would be great if the food portions are bigger. Overall it was an amazing experience and we would definitely be back!
Excellent food. Good service.  Would rate this as one of the best Indian food in Singapore.  Especially,  Lucknowi cuisine.
Arguably the best north Indian kababs and curries restaurant in Singapore. Their bhatti ka murg makes me visit them regularly.
Great if you like oily food

We didn t like awadh . Overpriced for very basic ambiance n place. In front of a food court in a mall. Interior was very low class.. no fine dining feel.. Justin B songs playing. Food was spicy despite requests for low spice. Dum handi veg was full of only paneer despite our telling the waiter many times discussing the order that we don t like paneer. Not going back there.
That was evening, so I just had a snack Samosa in this restaurant, its in Centerpoint mall level 1, its well maintained inside and good one. They treated well.

The most pathetic service. I placed an order at 730 pm. via deliveroo. We kept calling the restaurant but the phone was not answered. Even deliveroo could not get through. At 11 pm the app said delivered but nothing was received. And your restaurant does not have the courtesy to call me and explain.

Ordered on Diwali night, food never came. Tried calling, they never picked. We tried calling over 29 times. It s not the first time their logistics has gone down the drain as a result of surge in orders. Food here is great, I really hope they figure out how to manage the place. Would highly recommend to not order from here around public holidays, unless you are fine staying hungry
Ordered their Veg Set Menu thaali and it was good. You can try their non veg options also.. Their ghost Biryani is very authentic.. And yes the meat sourced is halal

Ordered 4 biryanis via Grab food yday. None of the biryanis were marked or labeled. My old parents who are vegetarian because of spiritual reasons ended up eating the jackfruit biryani which looked exactly similar to the chicken biryani. Really disappointing and ruined our Sat night dinner. Pls label carefully in future like other restaurants

The manager/ owner/ partner is pretty pushy to recommend dishes, the taste is just average, ordered two separate chicken starters and ended up getting exactly the same dish (one with bone and one without), even though the menu suggested something totally different. Once bitten, twice shy- I d not visit the restaurant again. Do note, the pricing is also pretty high compared to some better restaurants in town.

Amazing Ganpati thali and delicious food. Totally Worth the price..couldnt finish as there was more than sufficient serving for each dish.. special mention for yummy moong dal halwa..I would rate this promotional event 5 /5.

Tried Ganapathi thali. Horrible taste. Excessive masala. Curries were dark brown. Served cold, except poori, which was hot but partially crispy & oily. Rice was not so fresh. In my opinion far below average.

Not at all recommended. Tried their Ganpati Thali by getting attracted at the picture and vada pav which is priced at 25$ and realised is on the most average Indian restaurant in Singapore. The food was far below average in quality and taste and all the dishes served were very cold. Overall a regret to visit

The Paneer Tikka and Mushroom Gawlat Kebab were superb for starters...Just melts in your mouth. For the main course, we had the Subj Handi and the Lehsooni Palak Paneer with piping hot Garlic butter naans. We ordered 1 Ulte Tawe ki Roti also to try out, it was Overall great dining experience and very good service. Will definitely go again.
Horrible food specially biryani. Mediocre chef. Meat used for the dishes aren t fresh. Overpriced but not worth.
Very expensive

Enjoyed a great dinner in Awadh with both veg and non-veg options available. Tried their Gosht Galawat Kebab (mouth melting) and veg seekh niloferi as starters which was the best that day. Was sceptical with Chicken Biryani so tried the Nawabi Gosht Biryani which was good. Ended with a chikoo and guava kulfi, personally loved the chikoo kulfi. Great service by the staff and good recommendations of menu by the manager.
Very nice place to eat indian cuisine
flow

Had gone with very high expectations as I had read very good reviews,  but was left disappointed. Ambience is good. Service good but very slow. Limited options for mocktails. Had veg buffet, the buffet itself had limited options and mediocre food at best. From pricing point, its considerably high for 90sgd for 2 persons with the promotion. In all, would not recommend this hotel if you are going for buffet.

I visited Awadh with my buddy. Neha served us well. We ordered Paneer Tikka and one more dish as appetisers but felt full and did not order anything else. Its a clean place with lovely lights. It was not crowded. Overall experience was positive.

I have been planning to come to this place since last year before lockdown. So there was a lot of excitement before visiting the place. Ambience: Very simple. You may say that the only thing matters is food. But at a place where a cocktail costs more than the meal, then you tend to expect more from ambience. Hence, only 1/5 for it. Service: Very nice. They kept on asking what else do you need and all. But there is a fine line between good service and being too much pushy and not giving customer their space. A friend of mine felt that way. Hence 3/5 for service. Food: Galuti kabab and Mutton Nihari of this place is amazing. It has potential to be in top 10 of Singapore. But their biryani sucked. A complete waste of appetite. Overall 4/5 for food. In general, its a nice north indian place which serves good food. Some of these food resembles few dishes from Lucknow. But when you bring in the price point and compare them with other Indian restaurants. You would start to question, should you go back for another meal?
The food is average and the service is really bad. They took my order wrongly. Go there if you want the experience the OPPOSITE of Indian Fine Dining.

very bad experience. Food is not cooked, raw meat inner parts. Food delivered 50 minutes late. They did not pass phone number to delivery boy. Address was correct. Delivery boy was laughing that my number is wrong. Restraunt Did not pack chutney and onion. I ordered 4 starters only.
Uncooked food, Bad food for the name and average reputation of the restaurant. Chicken was not fully cooked and reddish flesh with gel like feeling was present.

Inedible food. Went there last month. Honestly guys, Ive had a lot of Indian food here in Singapore - and it is really difficult to run into a place with bad food, but this is it, this was the worst I did have, by far. Everything we ordered was simply disgusting and we ended up eating only around 30% of the food we ordered. Perhaps this place once was good (therefore the relatively good review), but it is certainly not now. On top of everything, as if not bad enough, it is also crazily expensive. They have starters for around 30 sing.
Good Indian food and top-notch service. For dessert - do try the kulfi! We had Rose and Anjeer - both were great!

To keep this short.. please DONT GO THERE!!! Food is so-so and definetly overpriced. Service is bad!! So bad!! And they cannot even get my order correctly and didnt want to acknowledge he made a mistake! DONT GO THERE.

Yesterday was the eve before Singapore implemented Phase 2 (Heightened Alert) restrictions. And when I stepped in the restaurant, the person who greeted me has his mask below his nose. Seems like he did not care about his safety and by extension the safety of his teams and customer. Do I need to say more?

Average food and very rude service. We ordered a chicken biryani and mutton curry. The person who served us might have misunderstood us and the food came as mutton curry AND mutton biryani. What is unacceptable is when we told the person about the issue, he insisted we were the ones who are wrong. Very very bad and rude service!!!!

Undeniably aesthetic nestled in a food court ambience. Colours in the environment were appealing to the diners. Food was good. Above all the staff members were absolutely courteous and were able to recommend some good food on the menu. My only concern and perhaps the reason which may abstain me from visiting the place again was the kind of food served in an environment which does not support a sizzling hotplate dish. It gives out heavy and spicy smoke effect . Diners sitting on the right and left of my table ordered the sizzler and smoke engulfed the whole place and I ended up having  irritant eyes which began to tear profusely. Unfortunately, I came in for lunch after my eye procedure and one could imagine the discomfort I experienced. I wouldnt mind when such sizzler dishes are served if there is proper exhaust system. Will be good for the restaurant to reconsider serving such dishes in the future. Being a vegetarian I was not comfortable being engulfed in such a smoke environment though! Although I was not fussy about being  doused in that smoke, I should say my clothes smelt bad and it lingered on me. Will be good if the management could be more sensitive to other diners and look into how to serve sizzlers with proper system in place. My heartfelt thanks to the staff members who were fast to react with wet tissues to wipe my eyes off the smoke irritants. Thk you again.
The food is not that great and quantity is less.Not worth the money
Good food, good service.
Extremely good service and food. They serve halal meats and the chefs are Muslim too. Kamram provided us with a warm welcome and service.

Just ordered from deliveroo - perhaps its authentic Lucknow food - but having tried multiple indian places  around Spore, this food was not at all tasty. The portion sizes are incredibly small making them incredibly over priced. There was a food item missing too - when i rang them they asked me to whatsapp a photo and gave me a landline number despite me double checking if thats the correct number - in the end it was not.. Very disappointing considering it has such a high google review - dont be mislead! Would not order from here ever again.
One of the worst restaurant , highly over priced and low food quality and on top small potion size.

We waited three months before writing this review because sometimes the service and ambience can distort what s ultimately average food. Suffice to say that Awadh s food was outstanding enough for its taste to linger well past 3 months. To someone jaded by the typical  north indian  food on offer in Singapore, Awadh delivers a shot of exuberant zing to the palate, with the food we ordered (recommended by the maitre d Arjan) hitting all the right notes. The Subz Galawat Kabab, Zaffrani Paneer Tikka, Bhatti Ka Murg and Subz Biriyani - all made for a meal most memorable. Apple Jalebi lives up to its exotic name - a superb finish to an outstanding meal. Skip the drinks unless you re in a mood to indulge. And we hope Awadh finds a larger, perhaps standalone unit, where its food and service can truly shine.
Overpriced and overrated!! The quantity per dish is only for 1 person. The food is not even tasty. Dont believe the good reviews you read as it can be written by anyone from the restaurant!
Wow, the food here was awesome, and a new experience for me to try Awadhi cuisine. Executed flawlessly, I cant wait until the lockdown is over to go again!

Unique and tasty take on North Indian cuisine. Bhatti Murg, Galawati Kebab and all the specials are very good. I also liked some really simple veg dishes like Sloo Gobi, Yellow Daal etc. they were exceptional and done very well. Must try for all, especially those who want to taste some great and unique Indian cuisine in Singapore. Great for family or with with friends or business clients. Mus try.

I ordered home delivery from this restaurant during heightened alert. The food was really bad, couldnt eat. Cold and oily and not at all worth the price they are charging. I ordered 2 curries, the paneer one had barely one piece of paneer and the kofta had one piece of kofta for a price of approx SGD 15 each item. I have had much better food at places with less hype.

Its a restaurant with good ambiance,where you can enjoy the tastiest food.everyone must visit it.

very nice

This is one of the best restaurants in this region. This is like home away from home . The food is delicious and you will always carve for more .

khana mast hai. good joint for spending time on wèekends

Enjoyed the food ! Will surely return for more
Very friendly staff and good food. Keep it up
Nice ambience and good tasty finger licking food

We went there for the lunch buffet during Id promotion...the food quality was very bad, worst service ever and the staff didn t even care to get the feedback from the customers. I think they knew very clearly they were just making money and not serving quality food and service. Very disappointed. They just lost a regular customer!
Good fool, good service, And Its Authentic, coz I am from Lucknow (Awadh) so I know it.
Fantastic service and food, their apple jalebi and galawath kebabs were the highlight. fantastic staff and chef providing personalized recommendations. Highly recommended.

This place over-rated. Not sure how. Please don t judge with the ratings on google.The taste of food is not at all authentic Indian. Price is also much more compared to other Indian restaurants. If you order home delivery Quantity is too less with worst quality. Chicken are not even cooked properly. If you go for biryani. They just put boiled chicken with half cooked rice with no taste. Chicken curry masala was also not cooked.you can smell raw flavour in all chicken items. It really spoiled my day by wasting my money.Please go though the review in food carefully in food panda before ordering.
Its ok. Menu seems limited. Maybe its just me.
Highly overrated restaurant. Nothing to crave about. Food was average. Their promotion lunchs are a trap. Avoid at all costs.

Had holi thali. Sweets were good. Rest of the thali was average taste wise. The thali for 2 pax will be supplied with only 1 roti(though they give some rice). With that roti, no clue how they thought customers will finish many curries provided in thali..and too 2 pax..

I would say the place is just over-rated. Please read the reviews in food panda and other apps before you order and just dont trust the limited reviews based on Google. Except the sides, the rest of the food we ordered almost tasted the same and smells the same flavor , even the deserts. The highlight was even the basic kadhai paneer didnt taste well here and the naan we ordered was not at all fresh and it was too hard . Just like previous day naan preserved and toasted.. The price was damn expensive for such a small portion. I am surprised to see good reviews on the taste of the food here.. . The total was 110$ for such small portions and only the sides tasted well here that too, its limited to 3 pieces while u get a good portion in other michelin star restaurants. Wasted our money here. Pls read the reviews carefully and order.
samosa and chicken briyani are meh, the rest are pretty tasty.
Love the place Awesome food and yes the staff was too good . Strongly recommended

One of our favorite restaurants in Singapore. The food here is great as per Singapore Standards and always reminds us of some good restaurants back home in India. Its moderately priced and the quality of the food seemed good. They can improve their ambience which as of now looks too crowded. Perhaps they should have a better chair and table. :) But the place is definitely a MUST TRY!
Over-rated and over-priced

Terrible experience. My child and helper both have diarrhoea after eating the butter chicken and chicken kebab here yesterday. We are going to the dr as its so severe plus he has to miss school! We had ordered in. Will never eat here again.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Jayati, Kindly share your contact details with us at our restaurant number and our management will get in touch with you at the earliest. Thank you.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The experience was very very bad. Not Recommended!!!! We went to Awadh by seeing the advertisement over internet for the Holi Brunch for SGD 55++ for two pax. After going inside, we came to know that its a one Thali (plate) where 2 people can share. It contains some 10 varieties of curries including sweet and curd  in a very limited quantity (very less for 2) and contains 1 naan (very small size) with some rice. (photo attached) Honestly, the quantity is not justified for 2 pax. Moreover the taste was very normal and nothing exclusive. I would really not like to go again for this much cost and for this less quantity. It clearly seemed to be a cheating where they want the people coming to order explicitly something extra because the quantity is not enough for 2 persons. They should actually mention this on internet about this. Lets say, if you are going officially or with the office colleague, how could you expect to share the plate. On top of this, they would be forcing you to order something from their menu like drinks and kebabs.
Lovely food and awesome hosts. Very warm and friendly atmosphere... Strong recommendation.. everyone should try their Awad thali Will  definitely come again...
You are looking at SGD 26 worth of food from Awadh. Portions are pathetically small. This is really a joke! Avoid at all costs.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear Laurent, we have 2 portion sizes - 3 pieces and 6 pieces which can be chosen while placing the order. The delivery is made based on this selection. Even though we are less that two years old, delivery -wise, we pride ourselves in being among the top North Indian restaurants in Singapore bringing a unique Lucknawi cuisine. Thank you for taking our time and sharing feedback, all feedback is appreciated and taken under advisement by our management.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Came here after shopping on orchard, and we were happy with the choice. We went with a big veg thali. It was sufficient for 2, just had to order an extra naan. We also tried a couple of cocktails -- mojito and a strawberry house special. Both were good. Only thing we didnt like was gulaab jamun, it felt a bit hard from inside, though it tasted fine. Although a bit pricey, but tasty food overall. Will come back some time. :)
Great ambience. Rice and the daal was awesome. Truly nawabi. Amit attended to us, was very cheerful and prompt. Great experience.
It was great experience with holi colors... food was great in taste ...

Nice spread for their Holi special Thali but service was very slow.. We had to wait for 20 mins for Rotis after our dishes were served. This dulled out our experience as food had already turned cold..
Good food, but mainly for non vegetarians. Ambiance is too dark for some of us linking. Service is good.

Pretty pricey place in Centrepoint - $8 for a naan so you have a rough idea of the price point. Food was alright but not exceptional, was expecting more considering the setting. Service was a mixed bag - while they were attentive, staff were incredibly pushy about getting the cocktails/ mock tails and my friend had to politely decline multiple times before they would stop. Not something I would expect in a restaurant, let alone one that is marketed as an upscale one. Even Al Ameen s doesn t do this..
Awesome authentic Indian food. Simply marvellous experience
Cozy nice place.

Great food, authentic Awadh. I love the lamb dishes here. Nice Indian decor, very friendly staff and service. Drinks are expensive and not worth it. The place is a little expensive at around $90 for 2. But They are always running some food promotions which I like.

Excellent dining experience. Our waiter was Harjyot and he was kind, welcoming and helped us with an excellent choice of food. The black daal was just out of this world. I decided to pack to black daal to go. Whole-wheat tandoori roti was phenomenal too. Couldnt get to the gosht awadhi biryani but took it to go with melt-in-mouth gosht kababs ... best for taking friends and clients out or just go in and dine oneself. This was an excellent experience on the whole ...

Amazing food and hospitality. The best  Awadhi cuisine I have had. Galouti kebab, Bhatti ka Murg and Shahi tukra are to die for. Definitely one of the jewels of Indian food in Singapore. I would highly recommend the dining experience.

Authentic food.. great ambience.. courteous and hospitable staff.. special mention of Mr. Kamran (Manager) and Ms. Anjali (Front desk) for their excellent customer service. Waiting for their live music performance to start.. Recommended!!

The staff serving us the food was great!! The starters were great too! Main course was pathetic and they did not even bother to talk about it !! Leave alone offering a discount for the horrible main dish !!
Paneer makhhni was good. The chicken biryani not so much.. sweet toast not so good

Fairly new restaurant. Neat decor inside and quite spacious. Their kebabs are probably their highlight - very good and very different to the standard ones you get elsewhere in Singapore. Good vegetarian options as well. They also serve a decent biriyani. Their other North Indian fare are at par with other good Indian restaurants.

The food was ok but the course meal at Chope was a scam. What they GAVE WAS A CURSE MEAL. It was too pricy for like 3 bowls that are like a size of a lemon with chicken inside. If you want to eat here eat from the menu and dont fall for the same scam by ordering some course meal.

Had a great experience dining here the other day on my birthday. The food was awesome especially dal shahi with naans. Lucknow style Biryani was too good for my palate. Staff is very courteous and service is excellent. Great place for any occasion. Thanks to awadh team for such a wonderful experience.
Poor service, unenthusiastic staff and over priced items....... taste is acceptable but first time I saw that even tandoori roti can be poorly cooked   won t recommend.

Amazing food and service. AWADH is truly indian authentic food and according to me this is the BEST indian food I have had in Singapore which actually related to the taste of India. Lahore Nihari, Apple Jalebi, Phirni, Batti Ka Murg are MUSTT TRY!!

5 stars for food - Must Try: BHATTI KA MURG, GOSHT NIHARI, LAHORI KADHAI MURG and ZAFFRANI MALAI PHIRNI 5 stars for service - Water with rose petals provided for cleaning hands at the beginning and end of the meal along with mango lassi shots in the beginning.

We have had the Kebabs in Lucknow, especially the famous Galawat Kebab, we were highly impressed with the Galawat Kebab Awadh has! ! It literally melts in your mouth, just like the one in Lucknow! 5 stars to that!! Also their Shaahi Tukda is not to be missed!! One of the best we have had thus far!! The service was also excellent!! Really impressed! Would highly recommend this place! It is definitely a must try!!

I came back to this place for the second time as i was really impressed with the food quality n the taste on my first visit. Unfortunately my second visit really disappointed me. I went back to this place on 14th feb which happens to be our anniversary as well. Since my husbamd is from lucknow i wanted to get some close to home taste. After we sat down we were informed that only set menus are available and it was 70$ per person. Since we alrdy reserved the place we went ahead with the set menu. I was surprised to find the food quality to be just average and in the main course it was chicken biriyani with some regular paneer n daal with egg gravy. None of the dishes delighted our taste buds. Since we cudnt even finish it we asked them to pack the food, and then came the second surprise - we hav to pay 10$ for packing. I mean where on earth ppl charge for packing when they hav already charged for the food. After some argument and unnecessary discussion we got that 10$ waived but it spoilt the mood for the rest of the day. We wud hav happily paid had the food taste and quality were really good. I myself recommended this place to several ppl, but m sad to say that i m never going to go back to awadh n neither u would recommend to anyone. You have let us down big time!

Awadh offers amazing flavourful food. We totally enjoyed our visit to awadh. It is mainly for non veg food but gives good veg options too. The food is rich and cooked with lots of love. Would surely visit again.
Service was excellent. Staff was friendly and guided us well through the menu. Being from lucknow, i could relate to the flavour of galawti kabab and it was delocius. Overall the food was tasty.
Best combo... Gosht galawat kebab with ulta tawe ka paratha followed by gosht biryani for all nonveg lovers ;-)
Delicious food..lovely setting of restaurant. Fantastic service from staff, always on hand to assist customers.

Excellent service from waiter/manager. Used burple 1 for 1 here with 4 friends. Got 2 meat dishes, 1 of the vegetarian dumplings, and 1 bryani with the deal vouchers. Added on a bunch of naan for good measure. Every food item was amazing in taste, and we added on 1 more dish+kulcha naan afterwards.
Good

My husband and I were very fortunate and extremely privileged to have had been able to have our wedding reception here on the 4th of December 2020. From the very first meeting with Ms Manisha and Mr Amitabh, we were blown away by their warmth and hospitality! Firstly, the ambience of the restaurant is amazing, what with the pretty chandeliers and all. Secondly, the food is wonderful! The way everything comes together is a tantalising treat for the Taste buds. Finally, the service is exceptional! They are very humble and attentive and helpful and they were so accommodating to our ideas and wishes and when we marched in that evening, we were so amazed at how everything had turned out. Its pretty scary to have had to plan a reception, albeit a small one but with so many restrictions, what with the pandemic and all, but everything was so smooth and effortless and we didnt have to worry as everything was well taken care of! After the reception, all our guests sang praises about the quality and taste of the food. Everyone enjoyed it immensely! They enjoyed the ambience, the food and how accommodating and quick the staff were. We are truly so deeply grateful to everyone at Awadh for having us and for enabling us to have a wonderful reception and most importantly for taking such wonderful care of our guests! In spite of the pandemic and restrictions, we were able to have a wonderful reception and we are truly blessed and thankful because for that day we truly felt like royalty! THANK YOU SO MUCH!!
Outstanding food and service. Ask for Harjoot  as your server - amazing recommendations and service.

Most of the food was not fresh or tastefully prepared for the price. The cottage cheese (paneer) was definitely far from fresh, the texture of the samosa showed its age, the roti and naan were sub-par and just a couple of the dishes we ordered were any good. You can get far better and fresher food at lower prices and consistent quality at places like Zaffron kitchen or the Indian curry house. Will definitely not recommend this restaurant. (update on 19 Jan 2021) Both my wife and I came down with a severe reaction after this meal. Had to rush her to hospital early this morning. I felt slightly ill but recovered faster.
Great service and Awesome food! Anjali was very friendly!

Special and heartfelt thanks to Manisha & Amitabh for making my ROM an unforgettable event. Food & hospitality of Awadh is first class. Owners and staffs at Awadh are very down to earth and friendly. Couldnt ask for more but appreciate! Thanks again!
None of the items we ordered were tasty. All were very bland. Prices are high as well.

The place is no where a fine dining restaurant. The food is oily, lacks basic taste ( forget presentation etc), over priced. Please keep your expectations to bare minimum or please avoid. More People will figure out quickly as the restaurant is relatively new. Lot of good reviews looks like from friends and family! so pls be careful!

This restaurant is located in Central Point Mall in Orchard Road. It s a dainty place with well lit and bright atmosphere and pleasant music. It s listed as a Royal fine dining place. The dishes were homely and tasty with just the right portion. There were quite a variety of vegetarian options. Starter: We tried the Fauladi Kebab and Paneer Kathi Roll. Both were quite good. The Kebab came with a green chutney with its nice spicy flavour. Main Course: We went for the Kadai Paneer and Lehsuni Motiya Palak. The Kadai Paneer is spicy while the Palak dish is rich and creamy. They complement well with any bread (Naan or Roti) and balance your palette. Dessert: Phirni comes in 2 flavours Malai Phirni was particularly the winner of the desert lot. It comes in another flavour of rose milk. In conclusion it was delightful dinner for us. The prices are comparatively on the higher side but seems okay for the taste and outcome of dishes.
Amazing food & service!!! Non veg curries are amazingly cooked with thick curry..  thanks to Inder for the great service

I would give 0 stars if I could. Received obviously stale phirni. Could not even eat 2 spoons as it was obviously spoilt. I called the restaurant and got the usual excuses. despite promises of a replacement match, no replacement arrived. Dishonest and bad customer service to boot.

Awadh feels like home. One of the best INDIAN restaurants to go to if you want real Indian food. True to its taste. I d start by sharing that their food is delirious. What we ordered was : Bhatti Ka Murgh, Gosht Galawat Kebab, Ulte Tawe Ka Paratha, Murgh Seekh Kebab, Murgh Chandi Tikka, Mutton Biryani, Butter Chicken, Dal E Khas, Rumali Roti, Cheese Naan, Garlic Naan, Magaj Naan. Their food is finger licking good. Amitabh who is the owner deserves a special mention here because we were to host certain set of folks and we needed a solid recommendation and wanted the chef to make the food with extra love. The food totally lived up to our expectations. Once you get to speak to Amitabh, you would know he is such a kind person and has some great suggestions to make. The staff Anjali and Neha are quite smart and patient too. Before finalising the menu, we spoke to Neha and she has a very calm demeanour. Just when she thought we were going a little overboard with ordering the food, she did not even hesitate to tell us that we might waste it, if we order more. How nice of her! :) They also sent us Milai Phirni which was a complimentary dish! Their food is so good that we literally went into food coma. I would highly recommend this place to you. Go book it now and I am sure you d come back wanting for more!
Amazing food , great ambience, authentic tradition!!

Went in to the resturant with alot of expectation, going by reviews and comments. It turned out to a huge disappointment for me and bunch of friends and spoiled our mood and celebrations. Worst taste you could imagine for an indian food. May khansama is much better if compared and at the half price or may be lesser. Review seems fake!!

This place is seriously overrated, and its hard to believe that they have got 5 stars. Well in my opinion this place has no relation with Fine Dining concept. Ambiance was equivalent to an ordinary Indian restaurant (ordinary Indian restaurants may serve you better food). All food items we ordered were super oily and doesnt have even close to 30% of authentic indian taste. Definitely its not value for money. Yummy...

The waiter never turned up with the dessert. Frustrated with the service we asked for the cheque, which itself came after 30 minutes. In summary its a big let down.

i wish i could give 0 star. i went today with my husband  to celebrate my birthday. they gave us food that was very cold it supposed to be warm right ? as u  are charging huge amount and claiming royalty exp. i really dont know eating 2 days old food is a royal experience.  you lost one client and never suggest any friend to go there.

Ulta tawa ka parantha was undercooked and the presentation of food was no where close what is shown on insta pictures. Highly disappointed with the food and service. Not too easy to spot them. I don t know much about Indian cuisine and their price level but this place is really very pricey for me. For the same or similar food, might have cost just half or less than half if you get it elsewhere. Service was reasonable and the atmosphere so-so. Yea I get it that maybe a lot of hard work and spices were in them, but really couldn t stomach the price tag. The broccoli appetizer is kind of special, first time seeing broccoli cooked this way, and it taste good. Food is definitely delicious especially the Naan, but will I come back again? Unfortunately, I don t think so.

One of the best Indian cuisines weve had in Singapore in the last several years. Authentic Lucknowi north Indian cuisine, melt in your mouth kebabs and such. Highly recommended for north Indian food.

My family of 5 dined there for the Festive Lunch Set meal advertised by the restaurant. There was really nothing special about the menu and service and food quality were far below expectations. Firstly, the staff took a fairly long time to give us menus and take our orders although it was a weekday and restaurant was running at half capacity. The waiters were not attentive and lacked the knowledge about the menu so that we could make our choices. Next, the food took an inordinate amount of time to arrive although it was a set meal - considering most dishes would be pre-prepared. The food arrived cold, only the naans were hot - we guessed that took time. The gulab jamun was cold and hard and none of us had more than a bite. The basmati rice was just a plain pilau - did not match the fancy name stated in the menu. Would give this place a one star if not for the saving grace - the buttermilk as an aperitif at the start was perfect and refreshing for a hot day. Just wished the staff were more active and genuine about attending to the customers. Maybe the main menu would have been much more appetising but it will take me some time before I try this place again as Ive had much better Indian food for equally priced meals.
Very good ambience. Indian celebration type. Good food and great sweets. Perfect for our friends here.

If I could give this restaurant 6 stars, I certainly would. Not only was their food exceptional, their service was outstanding. I had lunch there and had forgotten my wallet there with a considerable amount of cash in it. I hadnt realised until later that night that I had left my wallet at their restaurant. We rushed back and they had safely kept it with them. Not a single cent was taken and it was kept securely until we returned. Thank you, Awadh for such exceptional service, honestly and brilliant food. Will certainly be returning.

A royal dining experience at Awadh with delicious Lucknow cuisine  infused with rare spices and the warmest hospitality and service!

Awadh is the erstwhile name of Lucknow, where I grew up. So I was super excited to learn a restaurant attempting to showcase the cuisine of Awadh has opened here. I went with low expectations, because even in India, getting good Awadhi food outside Lucknow is very hard. I was very pleasantly surprised I must confess. The owner and his wife are from the state, and the chef is from the city, which definitely shows in the food. We tried the Galawati (translates to melt in your mouth) kebab, which is the acid test of any Awadhi restaurant. Ive not had this good a kebab outside of India. It is a tricky dish to get right, with a lot of spices going in to get it right. We also tried the Thali, which had a variety of chicken, lamb and veggie dishes, all with their unique flavors standing out (a very hard thing to do as most indian restaurants take a short cut and put everything in similar gravies). The dessert of rose phrini was also excellent. I will be back for sure. Give this place a try and experience an unique side of Indian cuisine which isnt easily available outside of the city of Lucknow these days!

Service is Excellent, Food is Good, Bit pricey but it comes with given location and service. There is an option for live music   there. Also to note, it is one of the rare places in SG where you get a warm water bowl for cleaning fingers....

Reserved a Friday night dinner with a couple of friends. I am a big fan of awadh cuisine having spent many years in Lucknow and was really excited to try this new restaurant whose claim to fame is Lucknowi cuisine. The galawati kebab and kalmi kebab were very nicely recreated. The taste was very close to the original. Thoroughly enjoyed the starters including the paneer wrap. The chicken korma was to the point and really good too. However, the dish that we were most excited about disappointed the most. The highlight of Awadhi cuisine is the Lucknowi biriyani of the likes of Idris and Ishtiyaque. Sadly the biriyani was normal Singaporean indian restaurant biriyani with yellow rice and chicken. The chef was so lazy that birista (fried onion) was the prepackaged dry one and not freshly prepared. The aromatics Lucknowi biriyani is known for were completely absent. Ambience is very basic as well as the service and prices are a tad bit high for the overall experience . I would recommend galawati kebab and korma.  Steer clear of the biriyani.

Good ambience , yummy food and cordial and excellent service. Price was on a little higher side for me but the quantity and quality of the food justifies that. Big thumbs up.. will go again.always recommend this place.
Enjoyed Kebab on Wheels for dinner tonight. Tried both veg and non-veg options. Manisha (the owner) was very warm and welcoming. Looking forward to trying the Brunch and Maharaja Thali options.

The food was enriched with flavour and zing. The Independence day Thali was incredibly scrumptious and the drinks were good too. However, their prices could have been more competitive. It was a little pricy. Their customer service was quite efficient and speedy. Overall, it was a pleasant experience and I would definitely recommend you to visit this place when they have an offer for a special occasion. There is a lot of vegetarian options as well.

Dear Folks & Dear Awadh Restaurant, This review is only for Galawat Kebab; As for other dishes people have already shared experiences that may vary person to person depending on their roots; their perception towards Awadh cuisine; and a first time tryer or a regular one. For people, especially Lucknowites like me who have tasted Galawat Kebab in Tunday and Dastarkhwan, it is my humble request please dont compare their Kebabs to the ones you will taste in Awadh, else you will be heartbroken. Those ones are mouthwatering juicy, very tender, carry a certain tickle and taste that cant be described, hence they are Galawat in truest sense. The ones you get to taste here are more like a dry version of those which wont have that juiceness, a bit more hard textured, and the authenticity or the tickle you will not find. As evident from the photo itself, you can judge the difference. I ordered Kebabs from this restaurant only after my research getting to know the history behind and therefore I had certain expectations. But after trying these, I realized have to wait another 6-8 months before I travel Lucknow. For other folks, I hope they will like these Kebabs :) I am not sure if this falls under any improvement space upon the restaurant since its a very delicate dish, but as someone who was rooting and feeling proud to finally find a restaurant in Singapore that can serve those authentic Galawat Kebabs all the way from Lucknow, I felt a bit disappointed and therefore this long review. Nevertheless, I wish Awadh best of luck in their success. -Vivek

Since we clearly said we didnt want that in our meal, we asked them to take it back. But the staff were too arrogant and said however we have to pay for it. I made a reservation here for a special occasion (since my husband is fond of Indian food). A list of things I was unhappy about: 1. Also informed chef about the same. Paneer butter masala - bit eatable but on the sweeter side. Panner pieces were too hard to chew. As had no other options so you what i meant. Masala tea - had masala missing. We were provided a complementary rasmalai but it so sweet thats its not worth it. garlic naan, cheese naan, paneer kulcha - were awesome.

Arrived on a Sunday at 3.30 pm. Serving staff, Rosia, was very friendly and helpful as I was looking through the menu, not knowing what to order. She recommended the $25.90 brunch with 1 Chaat/ Appetizer unlimited and 1 main course. I told her I do not like sweet food and she recommended the Samosa Chaat, a potato filled crisps with yogurt and chutney. It was delicious. My main course is the Mutton Bun Kebab, with minced mutton patty fried to golden brown, caramelized onions and buttered bun. This is fabulous too, not too salty but bun is a little tough, not for the elderly who have trouble chewing. The mutton patty is nice. I finished the appetizer and had a third of the bun then take away the leftover. I also ordered the Martini Bianco $12 as Rosia said it isnt as sweet as Martini Rosso. The drink is nice. After dinner, I ordered another Martini Negroni $17, which is supposedly a stronger drink that is more popular with guys. I like it too, strong and balance. For gals, they may want some lime juice in it. Total is about $65 as I had two alcohol drinks. It is still value for money, especially the brunch that is available on Sat, Sun and Public Holiday from 10.30 am to 4.30 pm. Highly recommend this restaurant to all.

Had gone with very high expectations as I had read very good reviews,  but was left disappointed. Ambience is good. Service good but very slow. Limited options for mocktails. Had veg buffet, the buffet itself had limited options and mediocre food at best. From pricing point, its considerably high for 90sgd for 2 persons with the promotion. In all, would not recommend this hotel if you are going for buffet.

I visited Awadh with my buddy. Neha served us well. We ordered Paneer Tikka and one more dish as appetisers but felt full and did not order anything else. Its a clean place with lovely lights. It was not crowded. Overall experience was positive.

I have been planning to come to this place since last year before lockdown. So there was a lot of excitement before visiting the place. Ambience: Very simple. You may say that the only thing matters is food. But at a place where a cocktail costs more than the meal, then you tend to expect more from ambience. Hence, only 1/5 for it. Service: Very nice. They kept on asking what else do you need and all. But there is a fine line between good service and being too much pushy and not giving customer their space. A friend of mine felt that way. Hence 3/5 for service. Food: Galuti kabab and Mutton Nihari of this place is amazing. It has potential to be in top 10 of Singapore. But their biryani sucked. A complete waste of appetite. Overall 4/5 for food. In general, its a nice north indian place which serves good food. Some of these food resembles few dishes from Lucknow. But when you bring in the price point and compare them with other Indian restaurants. You would start to question, should you go back for another meal?
The food is average and the service is really bad. They took my order wrongly. Go there if you want the experience the OPPOSITE of Indian Fine Dining.

very bad experience. Food is not cooked, raw meat inner parts. Food delivered 50 minutes late. They did not pass phone number to delivery boy. Address was correct. Delivery boy was laughing that my number is wrong. Restraunt Did not pack chutney and onion. I ordered 4 starters only.
Uncooked food, Bad food for the name and average reputation of the restaurant. Chicken was not fully cooked and reddish flesh with gel like feeling was present.

Inedible food. Went there last month. Honestly guys, Ive had a lot of Indian food here in Singapore - and it is really difficult to run into a place with bad food, but this is it, this was the worst I did have, by far. Everything we ordered was simply disgusting and we ended up eating only around 30% of the food we ordered. Perhaps this place once was good (therefore the relatively good review), but it is certainly not now. On top of everything, as if not bad enough, it is also crazily expensive. They have starters for around 30 sing.
Good Indian food and top-notch service. For dessert - do try the kulfi! We had Rose and Anjeer - both were great!

To keep this short.. please DONT GO THERE!!! Food is so-so and definetly overpriced. Service is bad!! So bad!! And they cannot even get my order correctly and didnt want to acknowledge he made a mistake! DONT GO THERE.

Yesterday was the eve before Singapore implemented Phase 2 (Heightened Alert) restrictions. And when I stepped in the restaurant, the person who greeted me has his mask below his nose. Seems like he did not care about his safety and by extension the safety of his teams and customer. Do I need to say more?

Average food and very rude service. We ordered a chicken biryani and mutton curry. The person who served us might have misunderstood us and the food came as mutton curry AND mutton biryani. What is unacceptable is when we told the person about the issue, he insisted we were the ones who are wrong. Very very bad and rude service!!!!

Undeniably aesthetic nestled in a food court ambience. Colours in the environment were appealing to the diners. Food was good. Above all the staff members were absolutely courteous and were able to recommend some good food on the menu. My only concern and perhaps the reason which may abstain me from visiting the place again was the kind of food served in an environment which does not support a sizzling hotplate dish. It gives out heavy and spicy smoke effect . Diners sitting on the right and left of my table ordered the sizzler and smoke engulfed the whole place and I ended up having  irritant eyes which began to tear profusely. Unfortunately, I came in for lunch after my eye procedure and one could imagine the discomfort I experienced. I wouldnt mind when such sizzler dishes are served if there is proper exhaust system. Will be good for the restaurant to reconsider serving such dishes in the future. Being a vegetarian I was not comfortable being engulfed in such a smoke environment though! Although I was not fussy about being  doused in that smoke, I should say my clothes smelt bad and it lingered on me. Will be good if the management could be more sensitive to other diners and look into how to serve sizzlers with proper system in place. My heartfelt thanks to the staff members who were fast to react with wet tissues to wipe my eyes off the smoke irritants. Thk you again.
The food is not that great and quantity is less.Not worth the money
Good food, good service.
Extremely good service and food. They serve halal meats and the chefs are Muslim too. Kamram provided us with a warm welcome and service.

Just ordered from deliveroo - perhaps its authentic Lucknow food - but having tried multiple indian places  around Spore, this food was not at all tasty. The portion sizes are incredibly small making them incredibly over priced. There was a food item missing too - when i rang them they asked me to whatsapp a photo and gave me a landline number despite me double checking if thats the correct number - in the end it was not.. Very disappointing considering it has such a high google review - dont be mislead! Would not order from here ever again.
One of the worst restaurant , highly over priced and low food quality and on top small potion size.

We waited three months before writing this review because sometimes the service and ambience can distort what s ultimately average food. Suffice to say that Awadh s food was outstanding enough for its taste to linger well past 3 months. To someone jaded by the typical  north indian  food on offer in Singapore, Awadh delivers a shot of exuberant zing to the palate, with the food we ordered (recommended by the maitre d Arjan) hitting all the right notes. The Subz Galawat Kabab, Zaffrani Paneer Tikka, Bhatti Ka Murg and Subz Biriyani - all made for a meal most memorable. Apple Jalebi lives up to its exotic name - a superb finish to an outstanding meal. Skip the drinks unless you re in a mood to indulge. And we hope Awadh finds a larger, perhaps standalone unit, where its food and service can truly shine.
Overpriced and overrated!! The quantity per dish is only for 1 person. The food is not even tasty. Dont believe the good reviews you read as it can be written by anyone from the restaurant!
Wow, the food here was awesome, and a new experience for me to try Awadhi cuisine. Executed flawlessly, I cant wait until the lockdown is over to go again!

Unique and tasty take on North Indian cuisine. Bhatti Murg, Galawati Kebab and all the specials are very good. I also liked some really simple veg dishes like Sloo Gobi, Yellow Daal etc. they were exceptional and done very well. Must try for all, especially those who want to taste some great and unique Indian cuisine in Singapore. Great for family or with with friends or business clients. Mus try.

I ordered home delivery from this restaurant during heightened alert. The food was really bad, couldnt eat. Cold and oily and not at all worth the price they are charging. I ordered 2 curries, the paneer one had barely one piece of paneer and the kofta had one piece of kofta for a price of approx SGD 15 each item. I have had much better food at places with less hype.
Amazing delicacy, food served is par excellence
Great food good service.
Very very nice food keep it up
Awesome food
A must go Experience
Awesome authentic food, great vibe 5star staff
Best place to eat. Fantastic food, rich tast.
Food is good
Great food. Must try.
Excellent

The food at Awadh was delicious. Each item we ordered was uniquely curated & packed with flavor. The desert variety was superb especially the kulfis. Will definitely recommend visiting if you enjoy Indian cuisine!
Wow,fantastic.nice.
Amazing ambience and super delicious food.
Awesome
It was an epic experience... value for money ... excellent taste !!! Must try!
Thank you so much for taking such wonderful care of our family during our visit!!
One of the best restaurants & I suggest my friends also
One of the finest restaurant for Indian Cuisine in Singapore. Delicious food and amazing ambience.
Its a restaurant with good ambiance,where you can enjoy the tastiest food.everyone must visit it.
Love the taste and presentation . Kabab platter is out standing.
The taste, ambiance and the experience is outstanding. Its a MUST GO  TO when Im Singapore.
A very elegant restaurant , with a great ambiance and delicious cuisines .
Great
